body.p:
The oxy_htmlContent form control supports the following properties:

 The resource needs
          to be a well-formed HTML file.

 This is a
          div element that has a unique id and is a child of the
          body element. The div element is the container of the
          HTML content to be rendered by the form control.

content - An alternative to the
            href and id pair of elements. It provides the HTML
          content that will be displayed in the form control.



p:before {
  content: oxy_htmlContent(hoverPseudoclassName, 'showBorder')
}
p:showBorder {
  border: 1px solid red;
}

An alternative example, using the content
      property:p#intro_id:before {
    content: 
        oxy_htmlContent(
            content, "<div style='font-weight:bold;'>My content</div>",
            width, 400px);
}
